<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="714" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Lyon</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 222.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            Liberian Legislature in joint session yesterday authorized the
                            appointment of a commission to visit the United States of America. The
                            commission will leave as early as possible after the adjournment of the
                            legislature in February. The appointment of the commission may be
                            regarded as the popular expression of the people.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ernest Lyon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>